The paper proposes a framework for measuring the real-time 3D shapes of soft robots using an embedded camera and deep learning techniques. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with the proprioception of soft robots. The use of an embedded camera and deep learning techniques for shape estimation suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the real-time computation aspect of the framework suggests control systems (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category.
